This is true both on the earth and in space.<br>
As soon as fusion becomes commercially viable<br>
existing atomic fission power plants will be replaced <br>
by nuclear fusion power plants. In space this <br>
will also occurr, And the thermonuclear rocket shall<br>
replace the atomic rocket in spacecraft propulsion.<br>
Then the fission plants will be decommissioned<br>
and will no longer be used.Atomic fission powered <br>
reactors,  and atomic powered  engines will be<br>
 consigned to the  mueseum of the early nuclear age.<br>
The A-bomb and the H-bomb however will continue<br>
